Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.86,0:00:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.93,0:00:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers, do you recognize me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.84,0:00:14.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you see this finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.27,0:00:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it? Can you answer me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.98,0:00:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.65,0:00:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.88,0:00:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that, Mr. Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.59,0:00:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.33,0:00:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming? What's coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.13,0:00:41.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.33,0:00:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster... is coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.14,0:00:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The monster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.24,0:02:28.00,Monster-Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(750,750)\pos(360,340)}Night of the Execution
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.40,0:02:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Junkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.94,0:02:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you're able to speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.18,0:02:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the four murders\Nof middle-aged couples
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.71,0:02:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in the past two years,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.41,0:02:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,you were seen near the scene\Nof three of them, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.65,0:02:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it, Adolph Junkers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.89,0:02:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Never mind. We know that\Nyou are a lock picker.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.30,0:02:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Your job is just to open locks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.47,0:03:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Slitting throats\Nin a single stroke...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.18,0:03:10.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is not something you could do.\NThat means there were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.11,0:03:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,other perpetrators\Nin addition to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.68,0:03:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that there would have to be\Nat least three people
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.55,0:03:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to open a strong lock,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.26,0:03:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and murder a middle-aged couple\Nwithout resistance...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.76,0:03:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost finished\Nmaking a list of men who use knives.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.50,0:03:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a matter of time\Nbefore we pinpoint your colleagues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.10,0:03:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether you talk, or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.61,0:03:43.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not what\NI really want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.95,0:03:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why four couples\Nfrom across Germany?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.28,0:03:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And why only kill\Nmiddle-aged ones without children?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.29,0:03:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Money and items were stolen,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.43,0:04:00.12,Default,,0,0,0,,but the amounts were too small\Nto split three ways to justify murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.57,0:04:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,How about it?\NWant to make a plea bargain?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.50,0:04:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,If you make a statement,\Nyou can escape prosecution...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.98,0:04:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked you to do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.49,0:04:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers. that's enough.\NThat's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.19,0:04:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to ask you to\Nend this questioning!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.73,0:04:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No, just a little bit more.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.50,0:04:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Please leave this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.83,0:04:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an order from\Nhis attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.14,0:04:45.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, all right.\NI'll come again another day.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.24,0:04:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But I will place a guard\Nto watch him closely
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.45,0:04:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so that he isn't poisoned\Nor that he doesn't disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.55,0:04:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Tenma, for some reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.09,0:05:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of trouble\Nseems to happen around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.92,0:05:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.73,0:05:05.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just a joke.\NExcuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! You, where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.11,0:05:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.31,0:05:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Doing things without permission\Nis going to get me in trouble!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.05,0:05:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Even patients need recreation.\NWe're just going out into the garden.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.49,0:05:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're worried,\Ndo you want to come with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.87,0:05:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a warm and pleasant day.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.24,0:05:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can talk, can't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.48,0:05:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,On days like this,\Nit makes you glad you're alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.68,0:06:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I need days like this,\Nor else it becomes unbearable.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.35,0:06:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I see people in\Nlife and death situations every day...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.12,0:06:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's easier for doctors to\Nfocus on fame and research.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.96,0:06:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to be like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.37,0:06:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I tried to gain a reputation\Nand do my own research...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.30,0:06:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought that succeeding in surgery\Nwas a way to fortify my status...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.41,0:06:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But after performing surgery\Non a certain boy, I changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.22,0:06:35.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He was the elder of fraternal twins.\NHe'd been shot in the head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.02,0:06:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved him, I was able to\Nreturn to being a real doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.93,0:06:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The weight of people's lives\Nare all the same...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.66,0:06:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,A doctor's work\Nis to save those lives...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.90,0:06:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.91,0:07:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You can start over.\NIt's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.69,0:07:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.36,0:07:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You and I are close in age,\Nbut you're like my old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.16,0:07:23.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.70,0:07:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like you're my parent...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.67,0:07:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly have a big kid, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.97,0:07:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When I was little,\NI wanted a mechanical clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.71,0:07:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:38.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.21,0:07:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind where a nutcracker doll\Nwould stroll out on the hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.45,0:07:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.79,0:07:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I would press my face against\Nthe show window of the watch store...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.49,0:07:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,My first break in was that store...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.83,0:08:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They caught me right away\Nand I didn't get the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.64,0:08:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But, after that,\Nbreak ins became my job...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.68,0:08:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At first, it was only because\NI wanted that clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.12,0:08:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I only wanted the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.35,0:08:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.90,0:08:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell the police everything\Nand start over from scratch...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.34,0:08:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.17,0:08:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,My associates, all of them...\NThey were all killed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.31,0:08:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Who killed them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.48,0:08:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you called "the monster"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.06,0:08:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Make this one yours, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.16,0:09:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through a lot of trouble\Nto set this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.63,0:09:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,She's the daughter of a member of\Nthe state parliament, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.73,0:09:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,She is beautiful and intelligent.\NShe's really something...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.27,0:09:11.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to meet her first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.34,0:09:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But... I guess...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:16.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I should do as you say\Nand settle down...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.81,0:09:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You should!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.85,0:09:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,For someone with your prestige\Nto not have a wife... Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.55,0:09:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.66,0:09:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The kind where a nutcracker doll\Nwould pop out every hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.13,0:09:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.47,0:09:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me!\NAbout the clock in the window...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:46.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's going on?!\NIt's already time for your date! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.25,0:10:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You can start over.\NIt's not too late.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.64,0:10:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer... Policeman on watch...\NYou're there, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.45,0:10:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.88,0:10:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But can you call Dr. Tenma, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.72,0:10:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.76,0:10:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Officer?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.01,0:10:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's late, but can I visit\None of the rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.88,0:10:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, of course, Dr. Tenma.\NWhat is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.78,0:10:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I found something good.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.07,0:11:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! What's the matter?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.80,0:11:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Get a hold of yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.44,0:11:21.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He's dead!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.74,0:11:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Candy...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.08,0:11:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.76,0:11:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.50,0:11:55.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's the same as the last time!\NPoisoned by candy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.54,0:11:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My patient's disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.57,0:11:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same thing that happened\Nnine years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.62,0:12:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.17,0:12:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.31,0:12:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's me, Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.28,0:12:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't come, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.02,0:12:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go back to the hospital,\NMr. Junkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.32,0:12:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.19,0:12:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Doctor. You mustn't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.56,0:12:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't see him, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:01.10,Default,,0,0,0,,"Him?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.50,0:13:03.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the one\Nwho killed my accomplices!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.24,0:13:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll be killed, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.68,0:13:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-Who's there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.19,0:13:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't, Doctor! You mustn't come!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.16,0:13:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long time, Doctor.\NIt's me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.60,0:13:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago, you saved my life,\Ndidn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.54,0:13:33.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Nine years ago?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.07,0:13:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you already forgotten\Nabout those twins?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.79,0:13:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.76,0:14:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, those twins...\NYou remembered.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.94,0:14:06.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!\NYou'll be killed!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.47,0:14:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What do you intend to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.48,0:14:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers is my patient!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.18,0:14:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.09,0:14:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Execute him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.32,0:14:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.36,0:14:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, run!\NHe killed my friends!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.43,0:14:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Wha?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.46,0:14:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We were hired by him!\NHe always called us on the phone!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.40,0:14:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,A large reward\Nwas transferred into our account
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.34,0:14:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,after each job was done...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.84,0:14:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'd split it between the three of us!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.88,0:14:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.24,0:14:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who ordered the murders\Nof the four middle-aged couples
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.55,0:14:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.15,0:14:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The police were watching me,\Nso we became a hindrance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:15:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already killed Fritz, the Slayer,\Nand Big Boy Boris!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.53,0:15:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just before he died, Fritz said,\N"We've been hired by a monster."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.30,0:15:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't think anything of\Nkilling people!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.84,0:15:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Run! Doctor, you'll be killed!\NRun, Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.24,0:15:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You talk too much, Junkers...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.25,0:15:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.58,0:15:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.15,0:15:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Junkers doesn't seem to know\Nwho you are, but I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.75,0:15:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I was your attending physician!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.86,0:15:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You are Johan Leibert, the elder of twins.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.56,0:15:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the son of Michael Leibert,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.46,0:15:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,former advisor of Commerce\Nin East Germany,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.74,0:15:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,who defected to West Germany\Nin 1986.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.57,0:15:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If we know this much about you,\Nyou can't possibly escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.81,0:15:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't add to your crimes, Johan!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Johan?\NI used that name before...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.22,0:16:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But that is not my real name...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.69,0:16:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.93,0:16:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My past must not be known...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.79,0:16:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Those four couples\Nand the Leiberts, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.00,0:16:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're different, Doctor...\NYou saved my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.21,0:16:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You're like my parent, after all...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.34,0:16:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Parent... me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.88,0:16:30.87,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, if it weren't for you,\NI wouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.59,0:16:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!\NYou mustn't kill!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.19,0:16:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.59,0:16:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,"Why not?"\NWhat do you think a human life is?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.73,0:16:44.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I saved your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.00,0:16:47.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I was able to go back to being\Nwhat a doctor should be!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.13,0:16:49.43,Default,,0,0,0,,By saving your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.50,0:16:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized that\Nthe weight of each life is equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.44,0:16:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No one has the right to\Ntake another person's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.31,0:17:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I've lived for many years as a doctor\Nwith that in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.62,0:17:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.06,0:17:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor, after that incident,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.00,0:17:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard you soon became\Nthe Chief of Surgery...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.13,0:17:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad that you were selected\Nas the Chief of Surgery.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.54,0:17:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it you want to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.17,0:17:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're here now because
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.34,0:17:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the Director, the Chief of Surgery\Nand the Chief died, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.75,0:17:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's really good...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.95,0:17:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be... You did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.29,0:17:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, you said it yourself...\NThis is what you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.70,0:17:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,When I became conscious,\Nthat's what you said
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.77,0:17:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That you hated them so much\Nyou could kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.27,0:18:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I am not wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.84,0:18:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That bastard... That bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.11,0:18:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He's better off dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.65,0:18:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,...off dead... off dead...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.12,0:18:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I did just as you wished, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.13,0:18:24.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor... I'm afraid, Doctor...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.33,0:18:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor... Save me, Doctor...\NI don't want to die!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.44,0:18:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.70,0:18:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I was supposed to have died back then.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.23,0:19:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You brought me back to life, Doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.17,0:19:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, this rain is terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.84,0:19:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate the rain. It washes away\Nall the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.48,0:19:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.99,0:20:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... That means,\Nfrom what you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.10,0:20:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1986, right after the Leiberts\Ndefected from East Germany
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.11,0:20:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with their twin children,\Nthe Leibert family was shot
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.41,0:20:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the parents died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.15,0:20:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,The elder of the twins, the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.18,0:20:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,was hit in the head\Nand in serious condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.15,0:20:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You operated on the boy\Nand saved his life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.99,0:20:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But, surprisingly, the boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.13,0:20:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,killed the director, chief of surgery\Nand head of neurosurgery
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.00,0:20:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with poisoned candy and ran away...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.23,0:20:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And last night, he appeared\Nafter nine years
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.30,0:20:49.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and killed a state police officer,\Nonce again with poisoned candy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.21,0:20:53.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And shot Adolph Junkers\Nright in front of your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.88,0:20:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the one who hired\NJunkers and two others
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.28,0:21:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,to kill the four middle-aged couples.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.05,0:21:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Johan Leibert.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.36,0:21:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's all of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.70,0:21:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,- Hey.\N- Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.60,0:21:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him go for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.98,0:21:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you ever think that someone with\NDr. Tenma's credentials
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.68,0:21:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,would ever commit such a crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.05,0:21:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,He has an alibi for the time\Nthe policeman was killed,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.29,0:21:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was no gunpowder residue\Non his hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.82,0:21:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,With this, the clue to solving\Nthe murders
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.96,0:21:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,of the four middle-aged couples\Nis gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.30,0:21:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,For the time being, shall we\Ngo after the guy, Johan Leibert?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.03,0:21:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge...
